<TEXT type="str">, 92, formerly of East Petersburg, passed away on Tuesday, January 24, 2017 at Brethren Village. She was the wife of the late William E. &quot;Bounce&quot; Bowers, Jr. who preceded her in death on January 21, 2016. Born in Columbia, she was the daughter of the late Harry and Helen Weiss Floyd. 
 
A clerical worker for various area companies, she was a longtime member of the Hempfield Church of the Brethren and a Columbia High School graduate, Class of 1942. For many years, both Betty and her husband Bounce were active members of the Hershey Region AACA and the Model A Ford Club. Through these organizations they enjoyed the comradery of a wonderful group of fellow antique car enthusiasts. 
 
She is survived by her daughter, Donna Naylor, Lambertville, NJ; granddaughter, Melissa, wife of Frank Crossen and their son, John William, Middlesex, NJ; sister, Beverly &quot;Toots&quot; McClellan, WI; and several nieces and nephews. She was preceded in death by a son, William A. Bowers and seven of her siblings, Harry &quot;Bud&quot; Floyd, Helen Floyd, Robert &quot;Eggie&quot; Floyd, Harold Floyd, Richard &quot;Sonny&quot; Floyd, Earl Floyd and Donald Floyd. 
 
The funeral service will be held from the Chapel of Brethren Village, 3001 Lititz Pike, Lancaster, PA 17606 on Thursday, February 2, 2017 at 11:00 a.m. with Pastor Dana Statler officiating. Interment will follow in Salunga Brethren Cemetery. Friends may view at the chapel one hour prior to the service. In lieu of flowers, contributions in Betty&apos;s memory may be made to the Brethren Village Good Samaritan Fund at the above address or at www.bv.org . 
 
Arrangements by the Clyde W. Kraft Funeral Home, Inc., 247 Main St., Landisville, PA. 
 
